sdpbpodcast/2012/hju20.mp3", "start_seconds": 7120.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-13T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/hju20.mp3", "start_seconds": 7120.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-14T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/hou21.mp3", "start_seconds": 11475.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-14T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/hou21.mp3", "start_seconds": 11475.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-14T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/hou21.mp3", "start_seconds": 11475.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-14T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/hou21.mp3", "start_seconds": 11475.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-23T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/sju26.mp3", "start_seconds": 6060.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-23T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/sju26.mp3", "start_seconds": 6060.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-23T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/sju26.mp3", "start_seconds": 6060.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SEN", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/sen29.mp3", "start_seconds": 1926.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SEN", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/sen29.mp3", "start_seconds": 1926.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2012-02-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SEN", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2012/sen29.mp3", "start_seconds": 1926.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 3566, "bill_version_id": 19776, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2012-01-23T09:23:12.043-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to establish provisions that a bond paid by, or on behalf of, a defendant in a criminal case shall be paid to the Department of Social Services to pay any child support the defendant owes. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 23A-43 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: The court may consider any amount of outstanding child support owed by the defendant in a bail proceeding when setting the amount and type of bond. Section 2. That chapter 23A-43 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: The court may order the forfeiture of all or part of a bond paid by, or on behalf of, a defendant who owes outstanding child support up to the total amount owed at the time the condition for the bond is satisfied. Section 3. That \u00a7 23A-43-25 be amended to read as follows: 23A-43-25. After the forfeiture of recognizance, bond or undertaking of bail, including an appearance bond, the prosecuting attorney shall proceed, with all due diligence, by action against the bail upon the instrument so forfeited. If money deposited instead of bail, including an appearance bond, is forfeited, the clerk of the court or other officer with whom it is deposited, shall monthly pay the money deposited to the county treasurer who shall deposit it in the county treasury. If the bond is forfeited against a person owing outstanding child support, the clerk, or other officer with whom it is deposited, shall pay the forfeited funds, up to the total amount owed, to the Department of Social Services Division of Child Support to satisfy the person's support obligation. This section is not to be construed to include bonds assessed for violations of traffic or other misdemeanor violations included on an approved fine and bond schedule adopted by a circuit court for use by lay magistrates and law enforcement officials for purposes of levying a fine and costs to permit a violator to submit a power of attorney in lieu of a court appearance. Bonds which have been submitted in payment of such violations, accompanied by either a signed or unsigned power of attorney, shall be deposited in accordance with state laws governing the deposit of such fines, liquidated court costs and surcharges."}, {"bill_id": 3566, "bill_version_id": 21368, "bill_version": "House Judiciary Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2012-02-13T16:10:07.703-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to establish provisions that certain bonds paid by, or on behalf of, certain persons with child support arrearages shall be paid to the Department of Social Services to pay any child support the defendant owes. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 25-7 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Notwithstanding any provision of chapter 23A-43 to the contrary, any cash bond deposited with the court, whether or not personally posted by the defendant, to assure appearance of an individual charged with nonsupport of a child under \u00a7 25-7-15 or 25-7-16 or subject to civil proceedings to enforce child support obligations, may, at the discretion of the court, be ordered paid to the Department of Social Services or the support obligee and applied to child support arrearages either as a condition imposed by the court or as a result of the individual's failure to appear as required by the court. 180 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.063 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 3566, "bill_version_id": 22388, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2012-02-29T08:18:37.073-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 3566, "action_date": "2012-01-23T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 19948, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/19948.pdf", "status_text": "First read